1
00:00:47,141 --> 00:00:49,439
Keifer's not going to school today
if he's the one you're looking for.

2
00:00:49,439 --> 00:00:50,774
Huh, what do I care about him?

3
00:00:50,774 --> 00:00:52,817
Besides, Keifer isn't
the one I'm looking for.

4
00:00:52,984 --> 00:00:54,194
Did that man come here?

5
00:00:54,194 --> 00:00:55,194
Where's Keiren?

6
00:00:55,197 --> 00:00:56,282
Where did you go?

7
00:00:56,291 --> 00:00:58,418
You know dad already
went back to the country.

8
00:00:58,543 --> 00:01:00,102
Are you Jasper Jean Mariano?

9
00:01:00,424 --> 00:01:02,468
The Watson Family
is asking for you.

10
00:01:02,474 --> 00:01:03,474
Are we all complete?

11
00:01:03,478 --> 00:01:04,854
We need your cooperation.

12
00:01:04,858 --> 00:01:05,959
Dad is up to something.

13
00:01:05,965 --> 00:01:06,965
What's your name?

14
00:01:06,972 --> 00:01:08,277
Uh, Jasper Jean Mariano, Sir.

15
00:01:08,345 --> 00:01:10,681
Your mom is kind of tactless,
isn't she?

16
00:01:10,878 --> 00:01:12,213
They're none of your business.

17
00:01:12,218 --> 00:01:13,719
I'll take full custody of Keiren.

18
00:01:13,725 --> 00:01:14,725
Sign these.

19
00:01:15,458 --> 00:01:16,709
I won't sign anything!

20
00:01:19,980 --> 00:01:20,980
Keiren, go hide!

21
00:01:20,986 --> 00:01:22,071
Hurry up, Run!

22
00:01:22,072 --> 00:01:23,072
Beat him up.

23
00:01:26,973 --> 00:01:28,266
Go on, pull that trigger.

24
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:30,282
Can you really kill a
defenseless student?

25
00:01:30,286 --> 00:01:31,286
Class is adjourned.

26
00:01:31,517 --> 00:01:32,852
Are you out of your mind?

27
00:01:32,856 --> 00:01:35,011
He's a professional hitman!

28
00:01:35,192 --> 00:01:37,069
What happened between you and your dad.

29
00:01:37,593 --> 00:01:38,899
Give me back my money!

30
00:01:38,906 --> 00:01:40,141
You're so greedy!

31
00:01:53,504 --> 00:01:55,538
<i>So what if that's what
he said to Ella too?</i>

32
00:01:56,411 --> 00:01:58,163
<i>That doesn't mean
he's fooling me.</i>

33
00:01:58,622 --> 00:02:00,320
<i>Aries is so annoying!</i>

34
00:02:02,959 --> 00:02:05,200
<i>But what if he really
is just playing with me?</i>

35
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:07,501
<i>No.</i>

36
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:09,504
<i>Keifer wouldn't do that.</i>

37
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:11,881
<i>He trusts me.</i>

38
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:14,801
<i>He even told me about what
happened between him and his dad.</i>

39
00:02:15,154 --> 00:02:17,429
<i>So I should trust him too.</i>

40
00:02:47,042 --> 00:02:49,210
<i> Aries already knows about us.</i>

41
00:03:02,104 --> 00:03:03,104
Hello?

42
00:03:04,391 --> 00:03:05,392
Are you crying?

43
00:03:06,631 --> 00:03:07,631
Huh?

44
00:03:08,594 --> 00:03:10,220
Your voice, it sounds different.

45
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:13,902
Did Aries do something
else to make you cry?

46
00:03:16,213 --> 00:03:17,213
No.

47
00:03:18,213 --> 00:03:19,589
He just scolded me.

48
00:03:20,217 --> 00:03:21,927
I’ll beat him up for you.

49
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:24,466
Stop it.

50
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,248
I'm dead serious, Jay.

51
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:27,562
I'm with you.

52
00:03:28,464 --> 00:03:32,093
If I have to face everyone in your family
just to prove that I love you,

53
00:03:32,118 --> 00:03:33,118
I will.

54
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:35,340
Keifer.

55
00:03:35,365 --> 00:03:37,788
Even if I have to get into a fistfight
with Angelo and Aries.

56
00:03:39,025 --> 00:03:40,025
You're crazy.

57
00:03:41,026 --> 00:03:42,026
But...

58
00:03:43,863 --> 00:03:44,863
Thank you.

59
00:03:46,050 --> 00:03:47,050
Wrong answer.

60
00:03:47,637 --> 00:03:49,571
What you're supposed to say is,
"I love you."

61
00:03:51,841 --> 00:03:52,841
You’re crazy.

62
00:03:54,103 --> 00:03:55,229
I love you, Jay.

63
00:03:57,413 --> 00:03:58,905
- To infinity—
- Keifer.

64
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:01,449
Is there a problem?

65
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:03,891
Uhm…

66
00:04:05,972 --> 00:04:09,078
Can we change the ending
of your "I love you"?

67
00:04:10,411 --> 00:04:11,584
That's too common.

68
00:04:14,908 --> 00:04:16,243
Alright, fine.

69
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,060
I love you, Jay.

70
00:04:22,255 --> 00:04:24,848
Until scientists find
the end of the universe.

71
00:04:26,992 --> 00:04:28,946
Is it because the
universe is infinite?

72
00:04:30,222 --> 00:04:31,222
Exactly.

73
00:04:39,164 --> 00:04:40,164
Don't worry, Jay.

74
00:04:41,024 --> 00:04:42,609
If Angelo finds out about us,

75
00:04:43,264 --> 00:04:44,264
I'll talk to him.

76
00:04:45,085 --> 00:04:47,921
Even if it ends in a fistfight.

77
00:04:52,494 --> 00:04:53,494
I love you, Jay.

78
00:04:55,489 --> 00:04:57,714
Until scientists find
the end of the universe.

79
00:05:00,309 --> 00:05:01,970
Mark Keifer Watson...

80
00:05:03,456 --> 00:05:04,456
I love—

81
00:05:05,129 --> 00:05:06,129
Huh?

82
00:05:06,135 --> 00:05:07,135
Ci-N!!!

83
00:05:08,222 --> 00:05:09,723
You're such a nosy kid!

84
00:05:09,848 --> 00:05:11,141
Unbelievable, Jay.

85
00:05:11,508 --> 00:05:14,677
I know I'm handsome,

86
00:05:14,683 --> 00:05:17,060
but you don't have to tell Keifer
that I'm actually the one you like.

87
00:05:17,063 --> 00:05:19,149
- Huh, really?
- So it's "I love you, Ci-N" now, huh?

88
00:05:19,156 --> 00:05:20,820
- Give me the other one, I'll make it even!
- Jay!

89
00:05:21,499 --> 00:05:23,066
My wound hurts!

90
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:26,212
You're really going to pick a fight
with me even when I'm about to leave?

91
00:05:27,622 --> 00:05:28,664
You're leaving?

92
00:05:28,989 --> 00:05:30,032
Yeah.

93
00:05:30,699 --> 00:05:32,791
Mommy said the condo is ready.
I can move in already.

94
00:05:34,229 --> 00:05:35,272
You're leaving me?

95
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:37,670
Well, you said you didn't want to
apply as my helper anyways.

96
00:05:38,749 --> 00:05:39,749
Ouch!

97
00:05:40,004 --> 00:05:42,634
- Stop hurting me!
- You're already treating me like one here!

98
00:05:43,258 --> 00:05:45,052
- Stop.
- Hurting you, huh?

99
00:05:46,090 --> 00:05:47,090
You know what,

100
00:05:48,408 --> 00:05:49,408
I'm going to miss you.

101
00:05:52,446 --> 00:05:53,491
Visit me, okay?

102
00:05:53,863 --> 00:05:54,863
Of course.

103
00:05:55,553 --> 00:05:57,860
You should be serving me this time,
you treated me like a helper here.

104
00:05:58,197 --> 00:05:59,198
So dramatic.

105
00:05:59,204 --> 00:06:02,129
- Yes! You've been treating me like one ever since!
- Not even!

106
00:06:02,137 --> 00:06:03,138
That’s not true!

107
00:06:03,148 --> 00:06:05,264
I've been so nice to you.
I clean your room.

108
00:06:05,636 --> 00:06:08,614
I wash your clothes,
prepare your food.

109
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:10,746
This room is clean
because of me.

110
00:06:11,535 --> 00:06:12,535
Do you want Yogorino?

111
00:06:12,539 --> 00:06:14,186
<i>I'm happy for Ci-N.</i>

112
00:06:15,472 --> 00:06:17,640
<i>I hope he'll be happy
in his new home.</i>

113
00:06:19,147 --> 00:06:21,817
<i>I also found a new home</i>
<i>with these assholes.</i>

114
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:26,046
<i>But because of the complicated situation</i>
<i>between me, Keifer, and Yuri,</i>

115
00:06:26,877 --> 00:06:28,518
<i>everything feels like
it's falling apart.</i>

116
00:06:35,909 --> 00:06:36,909
What's wrong, Jay?

117
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,510
You suddenly spaced out.

118
00:06:39,162 --> 00:06:40,162
Huh?

119
00:06:41,164 --> 00:06:42,164
Nothing.

120
00:06:42,523 --> 00:06:43,523
Come on let's sleep.

121
00:06:57,077 --> 00:06:58,187
<i> Jay-jay,</i>

122
00:06:58,901 --> 00:07:00,595
<i>you should talk to Yuri.</i>

123
00:07:01,229 --> 00:07:02,856
<i>If you're choosing Keifer,</i>

124
00:07:03,213 --> 00:07:04,714
<i>you need to tell Yuri immediately.</i>

125
00:07:05,721 --> 00:07:08,845
<i>Do whatever it takes to keep
this home from breaking apart.</i>

126
00:08:44,832 --> 00:08:48,695
[Ci-N singing off-key]

127
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:49,700
Okay, that's enough.

128
00:08:49,701 --> 00:08:51,313
You're really getting
on my nerves, Ci-N.

129
00:08:51,314 --> 00:08:53,816
Just shut up,
even for five seconds only!

130
00:08:53,816 --> 00:08:56,152
- Damn it!
- Wow, when you get all giddy, you get cranky huh?

131
00:08:57,019 --> 00:08:58,019
Whatever.

132
00:09:00,481 --> 00:09:01,481
You're so noisy!

133
00:09:02,149 --> 00:09:03,149
That hurt.

134
00:09:04,776 --> 00:09:06,921
Wait, you go ahead. I
think I forgot my ID upstairs.

135
00:09:07,214 --> 00:09:08,214
Wait for me outside.

136
00:09:08,387 --> 00:09:09,966
- Alright, hurry.
- Okay.

137
00:09:10,149 --> 00:09:11,149
Shut up.

138
00:09:11,439 --> 00:09:12,439
Hey.

139
00:09:14,506 --> 00:09:15,506
What?

140
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,266
You're getting married to Yuri

141
00:09:18,803 --> 00:09:20,335
You're just too beautiful,
aren't you?

142
00:09:21,738 --> 00:09:22,738
How stunning.

143
00:09:23,824 --> 00:09:26,232
You're marrying Yuri, and yet,
you also have Keifer.

144
00:09:37,569 --> 00:09:39,655
<i>Aries is right
even if he's annoying.</i>

145
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,485
<i>I need to tell Yuri the truth.</i>

146
00:09:43,110 --> 00:09:44,459
<i>I don't want to play with
his feelings anymore.</i>

147
00:09:46,638 --> 00:09:47,889
<i>That was never my intention,</i>

148
00:09:47,889 --> 00:09:50,767
<i>and I don't want to hurt him</i>
<i>more than I already have.</i>

149
00:10:06,342 --> 00:10:08,469
<i> How should I tell Yuri?</i>

150
00:10:10,648 --> 00:10:12,563
<i>Should I text him and say
I need to tell him something?</i>

151
00:10:16,087 --> 00:10:19,786
<i>Can't go to school. I have a fever.</i>
<i>Please take care of yourself.</i>

152
00:10:26,392 --> 00:10:30,139
<i>Damn it, what great timing!</i>

153
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:34,180
What's wrong?

154
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:38,386
Nothing.

155
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:42,933
Where's Ci-N?

156
00:10:43,518 --> 00:10:45,233
Oh, he went to Rakki.

157
00:10:48,254 --> 00:10:49,254
So,

158
00:10:50,201 --> 00:10:51,201
are you going to tell me?

159
00:10:52,205 --> 00:10:53,205
Tell you what?

160
00:10:53,962 --> 00:10:54,962
What's bothering you.

161
00:10:57,989 --> 00:10:58,989
It’s because...

162
00:11:00,094 --> 00:11:01,901
I've been thinking of
telling Yuri about us.

163
00:11:03,954 --> 00:11:04,954
What do you mean?

164
00:11:06,187 --> 00:11:07,625
I feel guilty.

165
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:09,920
I want to—

166
00:11:10,505 --> 00:11:11,745
I don't want to lie
to Yuri anymore.

167
00:11:14,551 --> 00:11:15,551
I understand.

168
00:11:16,362 --> 00:11:18,155
Even I am feeling guilty.

169
00:11:19,073 --> 00:11:20,073
Like,

170
00:11:20,098 --> 00:11:23,351
Why did we even end up
liking the same girl again?

171
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:27,965
I was planning to
go see him later.

172
00:11:28,618 --> 00:11:29,618
I'll tell him then.

173
00:11:30,096 --> 00:11:31,096
I'll take you there.

174
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:32,985
No need to, I can handle it.

175
00:11:34,696 --> 00:11:36,529
I know you can, Jay.

176
00:11:37,616 --> 00:11:38,823
But like what I told you,

177
00:11:40,196 --> 00:11:41,196
I’m with you.

178
00:11:42,156 --> 00:11:43,286
We'll face everyone.

179
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,834
But I'll stay downstairs.

180
00:11:51,127 --> 00:11:54,214
We might end up beating
the crap out of each other.

181
00:11:57,542 --> 00:12:00,253
But if anything happens, call me.

182
00:12:00,949 --> 00:12:02,122
I'll run upstairs right away.

183
00:12:05,266 --> 00:12:06,266
Thank you.

184
00:12:31,513 --> 00:12:32,513
Jay.

185
00:12:43,905 --> 00:12:45,765
<i>I want you to be happy, Yuri.</i>

186
00:12:46,783 --> 00:12:48,159
<i>I'll only end up hurting you.</i>

187
00:12:49,411 --> 00:12:51,663
<i>I can't bear to see you</i>
<i>get hurt anymore.</i>

188
00:12:52,831 --> 00:12:54,148
<i> I need to tell you the truth.</i>

189
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:55,833
<i>Right now.</i>

190
00:13:13,370 --> 00:13:14,370
I’m...

191
00:13:15,996 --> 00:13:17,143
I'm sorry, Yuri.

192
00:13:20,022 --> 00:13:22,190
Believe me, I really tried.

193
00:13:23,402 --> 00:13:24,428
What's wrong, Jay?

194
00:13:24,903 --> 00:13:25,903
What happened?

195
00:13:26,558 --> 00:13:27,558
But…

196
00:13:28,024 --> 00:13:29,024
What?

197
00:13:31,004 --> 00:13:32,338
It's really Keifer.

198
00:13:46,901 --> 00:13:47,901
I know.

199
00:13:50,527 --> 00:13:52,362
I knew from the start it was Keifer.

200
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:53,560
Right?

201
00:13:58,570 --> 00:13:59,643
Just like with Ella, Jay.

202
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:01,710
I just tried.

203
00:14:04,323 --> 00:14:06,909
But I lost again.

204
00:14:07,442 --> 00:14:08,442
Right?

205
00:14:14,674 --> 00:14:15,674
I'm not stupid.

206
00:14:16,873 --> 00:14:18,060
I know everything, Jay.

207
00:14:19,109 --> 00:14:20,552
Even what happened
on New Year's Eve.

208
00:14:21,736 --> 00:14:23,446
Even if you didn't tell me,
I knew!

209
00:14:25,549 --> 00:14:26,549
Yuri...

210
00:14:26,842 --> 00:14:27,842
Surprised?

211
00:14:28,521 --> 00:14:30,231
You thought only
Keifer had eyes?

212
00:14:31,732 --> 00:14:32,732
Yuri...

213
00:14:36,111 --> 00:14:37,111
Leave, Jay.

214
00:14:39,559 --> 00:14:41,575
I will let you continue
what you have with Keifer.

215
00:14:43,162 --> 00:14:44,705
But on our wedding day,

216
00:14:46,055 --> 00:14:47,151
you will say "I do."

217
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:49,688
Because if you don't,

218
00:14:52,189 --> 00:14:53,809
I'll destroy Fer Corp.

219
00:14:54,787 --> 00:14:55,787
- Remember that.
- Yuri.

220
00:14:56,392 --> 00:14:57,977
Yuri, you'll only get hurt.

221
00:14:58,193 --> 00:14:59,611
You're already hurting me, Jay.

222
00:15:08,418 --> 00:15:09,418
Remember this Jay,

223
00:15:10,938 --> 00:15:11,938
in the end,

224
00:15:13,211 --> 00:15:14,212
you will be mine.

225
00:15:16,044 --> 00:15:18,230
- Yuri, stop it.
- Just leave.

226
00:15:19,852 --> 00:15:21,087
Leave.

227
00:15:23,318 --> 00:15:24,903
You're just like Ella.

228
00:15:27,652 --> 00:15:28,652
You lead people on.

229
00:15:54,830 --> 00:15:55,845
Keifer…

230
00:15:58,213 --> 00:16:00,076
He doesn't want to
call off the wedding.

231
00:16:02,253 --> 00:16:04,672
Just say the word,
I'll go up there and punch him.

232
00:16:05,523 --> 00:16:07,633
You said you didn't want trouble.

233
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:10,970
Then stop crying.

234
00:16:11,283 --> 00:16:12,820
I hate seeing you cry.

235
00:16:25,998 --> 00:16:27,291
Your nose is runny.

236
00:16:28,162 --> 00:16:29,608
Fuck you.

237
00:16:32,473 --> 00:16:33,473
Jay,

238
00:16:35,674 --> 00:16:37,163
don't worry about the wedding.

239
00:16:38,511 --> 00:16:40,082
We still have enough time

240
00:16:40,304 --> 00:16:43,377
to figure out how
to stop it, okay?

241
00:16:50,417 --> 00:16:51,719
Wipe your snot.

242
00:16:52,635 --> 00:16:55,513
- It's just a little.
- You're gross.

243
00:17:03,481 --> 00:17:04,481
Jay.

244
00:17:05,314 --> 00:17:06,315
What?

245
00:17:09,187 --> 00:17:10,313
I talked to Percy.

246
00:17:13,099 --> 00:17:14,392
Remember my promise

247
00:17:15,131 --> 00:17:16,818
about getting your
father's information?

248
00:17:18,452 --> 00:17:19,452
Well,

249
00:17:19,878 --> 00:17:24,043
I got his contact
and called him.

250
00:17:25,974 --> 00:17:28,268
But his secretary was
the one who answered.

251
00:17:35,606 --> 00:17:37,107
<i>Hello, you've reached Mr. Mariano.</i>

252
00:17:37,107 --> 00:17:38,400
<i>May I know who's on the line?</i>

253
00:17:38,776 --> 00:17:39,934
<i>This is Keifer Watson.</i>

254
00:17:40,527 --> 00:17:42,029
<i>May I speak to Mr. Mariano?</i>

255
00:17:42,029 --> 00:17:43,029
<i>This is urgent.</i>

256
00:17:43,217 --> 00:17:44,301
<i>Keifer.</i>

257
00:17:44,301 --> 00:17:45,390
<i>How are you?</i>

258
00:17:46,804 --> 00:17:50,862
<i>Oh crap, you're making me cry!</i>

259
00:17:51,183 --> 00:17:52,183
<i>Who’s this?</i>

260
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:53,626
<i>You forgot about me already?</i>

261
00:17:54,353 --> 00:17:58,119
<i>Has it really been that long that </i>
<i>you forgot about your dead friend?</i>

262
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:00,733
<i>My heart!</i>

263
00:18:01,461 --> 00:18:02,461
<i>I’m in pain!</i>

264
00:18:02,486 --> 00:18:03,486
<i>Percy?</i>

265
00:18:04,321 --> 00:18:05,321
<i>Finally!</i>

266
00:18:06,260 --> 00:18:08,638
<i>I thought you'd never remember
my handsome voice.</i>

267
00:18:08,784 --> 00:18:10,285
<i>I have no time for your shit.</i>

268
00:18:10,285 --> 00:18:12,550
<i>I need to speak with
Mr. Mariano, now!</i>

269
00:18:16,334 --> 00:18:18,169
<i>Mark Keifer Watson, </i>

270
00:18:19,294 --> 00:18:20,712
<i>You haven't changed one bit. </i>

271
00:18:21,046 --> 00:18:22,548
<i>- Still so bossy.</i>
<i>- Percy!</i>

272
00:18:22,881 --> 00:18:24,716
<i>Still thinking you're the king?</i>

273
00:18:25,968 --> 00:18:28,929
<i>I'm talking about
Jay-jay's father, not you.</i>

274
00:18:28,929 --> 00:18:31,640
<i>Keifer, you're already
talking to Mr. Mariano.</i>

275
00:18:31,893 --> 00:18:33,738
<i>Well. I have to go.</i>

276
00:18:34,601 --> 00:18:35,601
<i>Don't worry,</i>

277
00:18:36,019 --> 00:18:37,479
<i>we'll be back soon.</i>

278
00:18:37,833 --> 00:18:40,586
<i>And when we do, </i>
<i>we'll take Jay-jay back from you.</i>

279
00:18:43,841 --> 00:18:45,384
Take what back?

280
00:18:45,976 --> 00:18:47,978
I don't understand.

281
00:18:49,779 --> 00:18:50,779
I'm also confused.

282
00:18:52,808 --> 00:18:54,434
I guess we just have to wait and see.

283
00:18:57,508 --> 00:18:59,760
I'm tired of waiting, Keifer.

284
00:19:04,237 --> 00:19:06,181
Just... please be patient, Jay.

285
00:19:20,042 --> 00:19:21,042
Shall we go?

286
00:19:21,419 --> 00:19:22,419
Let's go.

287
00:19:41,745 --> 00:19:42,955
Hey, it's Angelo!

288
00:19:43,899 --> 00:19:46,986
Hurry, lift it up!

289
00:19:47,011 --> 00:19:49,222
- Hurry, lift it up!
- Leave it up to me, I'll take care of Jay-jay.

290
00:19:54,493 --> 00:19:57,154
Maybe in 2 weeks,
we'll inform Jay-jay.

291
00:20:02,818 --> 00:20:04,477
You said you were
going to fight him.

292
00:20:04,816 --> 00:20:05,984
Why are you hiding?

293
00:20:06,422 --> 00:20:08,582
Of course I need to prepare,
he's strong!

294
00:20:09,127 --> 00:20:10,822
"Of course I need to prepare,
he's strong!"

295
00:20:13,796 --> 00:20:16,623
And may I remind you
of our offices in Guam.

296
00:20:19,143 --> 00:20:22,521
I'll see you soon, bye.

297
00:20:27,723 --> 00:20:28,870
He's gone.

298
00:20:29,155 --> 00:20:31,032
You can stop hiding now.

299
00:20:33,124 --> 00:20:34,124
Let’s go.

300
00:20:36,076 --> 00:20:37,076
Ouch!

301
00:20:38,181 --> 00:20:39,181
Hurry up.

302
00:20:42,060 --> 00:20:43,492
Oh, Aries.

303
00:20:48,723 --> 00:20:49,723
Come on, Jay-jay.

304
00:20:58,314 --> 00:20:59,314
I love you, Jay.

305
00:21:00,036 --> 00:21:02,261
Until scientists find
the end of the universe.

306
00:21:26,635 --> 00:21:27,845
- What even is this?
- So dramatic.

307
00:21:27,845 --> 00:21:28,887
Are you carrying your
entire house inside this?

308
00:21:28,887 --> 00:21:29,887
It’s so heavy!

309
00:21:31,128 --> 00:21:32,128
Ouch! Damn It!

310
00:21:33,198 --> 00:21:34,877
- Jay.
- What?

311
00:21:36,679 --> 00:21:41,425
I know I'm handsome, and you
might have fallen for me already...

312
00:21:41,610 --> 00:21:45,054
But you didn't have to tell Keifer
that I'm the one you love.

313
00:21:45,468 --> 00:21:46,594
Fuck you!

314
00:21:46,695 --> 00:21:47,932
Jay!

315
00:21:48,155 --> 00:21:49,364
You're such an idiot!

316
00:21:49,364 --> 00:21:51,560
- So full of yourself!
- You're just jealous of my belly fat!

317
00:21:51,563 --> 00:21:53,732
I've got belly fat too, dumbass!

318
00:21:53,732 --> 00:21:55,608
Then why are you pinching
mine if you have one?

319
00:21:55,608 --> 00:21:57,541
"Then why are you pinching
mine if you have one?"

320
00:21:57,548 --> 00:22:00,694
- Whatever!
- Jealous much, Jay-jay?

321
00:22:01,370 --> 00:22:03,890
Why are you even teasing me?
I'm already helping you carry this!

322
00:22:05,612 --> 00:22:08,156
You should've carried
this all on your own!

323
00:22:08,156 --> 00:22:09,324
What's in this anyways?

324
00:22:09,324 --> 00:22:12,702
This luggage is insanely heavy!

325
00:22:12,702 --> 00:22:13,702
Ouch!

326
00:22:16,153 --> 00:22:17,153
Ouch!

327
00:22:22,493 --> 00:22:23,493
Jay!

328
00:22:23,619 --> 00:22:24,619
It's your fault!

329
00:22:24,619 --> 00:22:26,245
Aries, I'm sorry!

330
00:22:26,245 --> 00:22:27,245
Aries!

331
00:22:27,826 --> 00:22:28,994
Are you okay?

332
00:22:28,994 --> 00:22:30,246
Sorry!

333
00:22:30,246 --> 00:22:31,246
That hurts!

334
00:22:31,253 --> 00:22:32,963
What hurts?

335
00:22:32,963 --> 00:22:34,395
Where did that come from anyway?

336
00:22:34,602 --> 00:22:36,437
Sorry, that was mine.

337
00:22:36,437 --> 00:22:38,772
Even on your way out,
you're still a nuisance!

338
00:22:38,772 --> 00:22:40,858
It's my fault, I'm sorry.

339
00:22:40,858 --> 00:22:42,110
Don't yell at the kid.

340
00:22:42,818 --> 00:22:43,862
Sorry.

341
00:22:49,488 --> 00:22:51,410
You weren't being careful.

342
00:22:51,410 --> 00:22:52,746
You brought too much.

343
00:22:55,479 --> 00:22:56,481
Let's go?

344
00:22:56,766 --> 00:22:58,335
Dr. Peralta is waiting for you.

345
00:22:58,688 --> 00:23:00,498
- Alright.
- You're coming with us, right?

346
00:23:00,523 --> 00:23:01,523
Yes

347
00:23:01,813 --> 00:23:02,813
Then why are you
still dressed like that?

348
00:23:03,358 --> 00:23:04,358
Go change.

349
00:23:07,150 --> 00:23:08,150
I've got this.

350
00:23:09,156 --> 00:23:10,290
l’ll just get the other two.

351
00:23:16,494 --> 00:23:17,627
Thank you,

352
00:23:18,144 --> 00:23:19,437
for driving Ci-N home.

353
00:23:20,166 --> 00:23:21,610
Thanks for the free food, too.

354
00:23:21,913 --> 00:23:22,913
You want some?

355
00:23:24,711 --> 00:23:26,656
Finally, I get to eat in peace.

356
00:23:27,003 --> 00:23:28,839
No spoiled brat
trying to steal my food.

357
00:23:29,636 --> 00:23:31,971
Maybe finish chewing what's in
your mouth before you speak.

358
00:23:34,993 --> 00:23:38,194
<i>Is there really no other
way to save the company?</i>

359
00:23:39,113 --> 00:23:40,273
<i>To save you?</i>

360
00:23:41,657 --> 00:23:42,657
Jay-jay?

361
00:23:45,875 --> 00:23:48,583
Don't be scared, I'm Tiger.

362
00:23:48,711 --> 00:23:50,513
And I own this place.

363
00:23:50,521 --> 00:23:51,805
Jay-jay, pizza.

364
00:23:53,215 --> 00:23:54,215
Tiger?

365
00:23:54,614 --> 00:23:56,491
I knew it was you!

366
00:24:00,722 --> 00:24:02,483
- Leo?
- Angelo?

367
00:24:02,488 --> 00:24:05,033
- Long time no see, bro!
- Leo, long time!

368
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:06,118
How are you?

369
00:24:06,292 --> 00:24:08,544
I'm good, what are you doing here?

370
00:24:09,091 --> 00:24:12,405
Just met with someone,
paid off some things.

371
00:24:12,430 --> 00:24:14,537
Then bought a few stuff.

372
00:24:15,330 --> 00:24:17,205
You're really everywhere, huh?

373
00:24:17,374 --> 00:24:18,625
Anyways, it's nice seeing you here.

374
00:24:18,625 --> 00:24:19,792
Nice to see you.

375
00:24:24,746 --> 00:24:25,965
I'll poke your eyes out!

376
00:24:26,226 --> 00:24:28,270
You're so cute,
you really love pizza.

377
00:24:28,270 --> 00:24:30,010
Can I have one? Just one.

378
00:24:31,065 --> 00:24:32,790
Wait.

379
00:24:33,275 --> 00:24:34,360
You know each other?

380
00:24:35,488 --> 00:24:39,242
Yeah, I met her when
they went to Kingsground.

381
00:24:40,827 --> 00:24:44,082
<i>Fuck, Jay-jay! Play dead before</i>
<i>Angelo actually kills you.</i>

382
00:24:44,107 --> 00:24:46,776
I'm just here, are you at the parking lot?

383
00:24:46,776 --> 00:24:48,362
Well, would you look at that.
Alvin!

384
00:24:50,080 --> 00:24:51,080
How are you?

385
00:24:51,165 --> 00:24:52,165
Alvin!

386
00:24:52,173 --> 00:24:53,492
Oh, Angelo!

387
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:54,950
Hi Jay.

388
00:24:57,496 --> 00:24:59,039
Leo?

389
00:24:59,039 --> 00:25:02,417
Hey, don't look at me like
I'm some horrible person.

390
00:25:03,837 --> 00:25:06,923
Sorry, you just look older.

391
00:25:08,091 --> 00:25:10,300
Well, how was it?

392
00:25:11,678 --> 00:25:16,099
We had a four-year gap
back in HVIS, right?

393
00:25:16,099 --> 00:25:18,602
But you really do
look older and uglier.

394
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:21,019
- Right?
- Uglier?!

395
00:25:21,292 --> 00:25:22,501
Are you crazy?

396
00:25:22,501 --> 00:25:23,919
Hey, hey!

397
00:25:23,919 --> 00:25:26,233
He's our senior, show some respect.

398
00:25:27,144 --> 00:25:28,687
Respect, my ass.

399
00:25:29,271 --> 00:25:30,821
Angelo, am I really ugly?

400
00:25:31,161 --> 00:25:34,254
Of course not, just very ugly.

401
00:25:36,946 --> 00:25:39,871
Whatever,
you guys are just insecure.

402
00:25:42,159 --> 00:25:43,417
Because I'm too handsome.

403
00:25:43,668 --> 00:25:44,925
Whatever, losers.

404
00:25:45,259 --> 00:25:46,878
Hello, are you there already?

405
00:25:47,978 --> 00:25:48,978
I'll see you guys.

406
00:25:48,985 --> 00:25:50,048
That was hilarious!

407
00:25:50,746 --> 00:25:52,561
You guys are funny.

408
00:25:55,189 --> 00:25:56,189
You.

409
00:25:57,608 --> 00:25:59,485
You went to Kingsground
without my permission?

410
00:25:59,485 --> 00:26:01,028
You're really stubborn, huh!

411
00:26:01,028 --> 00:26:02,894
- But that was a long time ago!
- Even so.

412
00:26:03,405 --> 00:26:04,896
You're such a stubborn little shit!

413
00:26:05,229 --> 00:26:06,303
You're in so much trouble.

414
00:26:11,705 --> 00:26:12,779
Hello, mom?

415
00:26:12,998 --> 00:26:14,124
We're about to go home.

416
00:26:14,124 --> 00:26:16,251
Huh?! What happened?

417
00:26:17,294 --> 00:26:18,452
Okay, we're on our way.

418
00:26:18,954 --> 00:26:20,163
What's the matter?

419
00:26:21,521 --> 00:26:23,123
Aries was rushed to the hospital.

420
00:26:23,234 --> 00:26:24,722
- Why? What happened?
- I don't know.

421
00:26:34,161 --> 00:26:35,381
<i>A complication with his lungs?</i>

422
00:26:36,137 --> 00:26:37,137
<i>Since when?</i>

423
00:26:38,287 --> 00:26:41,791
<i>I didn't understand what Auntie Gema</i>
<i>and the doctor were talking about.</i>

424
00:26:47,156 --> 00:26:48,156
Jay.

425
00:26:49,325 --> 00:26:50,325
What's wrong?

426
00:26:53,564 --> 00:26:55,071
You're thinking about it again?

427
00:26:57,888 --> 00:27:00,911
It's because of Aries,
he's in the hospital.

428
00:27:01,088 --> 00:27:02,381
Why, what happened?

429
00:27:04,353 --> 00:27:07,273
He apparently has
Pulmonary Fibrosis.

430
00:27:07,957 --> 00:27:09,132
I don't understand it either.

431
00:27:18,784 --> 00:27:20,389
Aries is going to be okay.

432
00:27:22,177 --> 00:27:23,262
He's Aries.

433
00:27:30,630 --> 00:27:32,985
Wow, so sweet.

434
00:27:35,650 --> 00:27:37,470
- What’s funny?
- You're blushing again, Jay!

435
00:27:37,470 --> 00:27:38,470
No, I'm not!

436
00:27:41,515 --> 00:27:43,245
Look at Jay-jay, she's blushing.

437
00:27:45,823 --> 00:27:48,576
- She's turning red.
<i>- Another thing I'm worried about is Yuri.</i>

438
00:27:49,931 --> 00:27:52,141
<i>What if he goes back
to how he was before?</i>

439
00:27:53,027 --> 00:27:57,342
<i>What if he goes to see
Leo, a.k.a Tiger, again?</i>

440
00:27:57,719 --> 00:27:59,011
<i>I hope not.</i>

441
00:27:59,992 --> 00:28:03,432
Okay everyone, fix your chairs.

442
00:28:04,948 --> 00:28:06,575
I said fix your chairs!

443
00:28:07,868 --> 00:28:09,661
Bring out your books.

444
00:28:11,497 --> 00:28:13,248
Please be quiet.

445
00:28:14,291 --> 00:28:15,777
I said bring out your books.

446
00:28:18,128 --> 00:28:22,382
If the demand is less than the supply,
the price will go down.

447
00:28:22,382 --> 00:28:25,376
And if the supply is
greater than the demand,

448
00:28:25,934 --> 00:28:27,289
the price will go up.

449
00:28:41,026 --> 00:28:42,361
Ma'am!

450
00:28:42,361 --> 00:28:44,154
May I go out, please?

451
00:28:44,154 --> 00:28:46,016
No, you may not.

452
00:28:47,407 --> 00:28:48,407
Hey!

453
00:28:58,459 --> 00:28:59,710
Class!

454
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:01,757
Mr. Watson and Ms. Mariano,

455
00:29:01,782 --> 00:29:02,824
what’s going on?

456
00:29:02,824 --> 00:29:05,327
Actually, it's Mrs. Watson.

457
00:29:09,022 --> 00:29:10,749
“Mrs. Watson!”

458
00:29:11,124 --> 00:29:13,043
Ci-N, help me!

459
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,422
Behave, everyone!

460
00:29:18,340 --> 00:29:20,480
Ms. Mariano, please take your seat.

461
00:29:22,761 --> 00:29:26,431
And you Mr. Watson, if you're really
listening to this class.

462
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:29,685
Can you please explain
the definition of profit?

463
00:29:30,951 --> 00:29:31,951
There, serves you right.

464
00:29:32,344 --> 00:29:33,344
Sure.

465
00:29:33,804 --> 00:29:36,765
Profit is the financial
gain a business makes.

466
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:40,711
It is calculated by subtracting
total costs from total revenue.

467
00:29:43,104 --> 00:29:46,644
Wow!

468
00:29:48,139 --> 00:29:49,622
What's "profit" in Tagalog?

469
00:29:54,395 --> 00:29:56,045
“Profit," "Income."

470
00:29:56,872 --> 00:29:58,522
How about "expensive profit?"

471
00:30:02,445 --> 00:30:03,488
<i>[in Tagalog] “I love you?”</i>

472
00:30:04,030 --> 00:30:05,740
Nice one, Keifer!

473
00:30:05,740 --> 00:30:06,972
I love you, too.

474
00:30:09,285 --> 00:30:11,393
"I love you!”

475
00:30:16,991 --> 00:30:18,808
Class, settle down!

476
00:30:26,594 --> 00:30:28,095
Such a stunner!

477
00:30:40,608 --> 00:30:43,425
- I got here first.
- Fall in line properly!

478
00:30:47,073 --> 00:30:50,474
Wait, where are Drew,
Denzel, and Mayo?

479
00:30:50,785 --> 00:30:51,828
Did you see them?

480
00:30:52,703 --> 00:30:53,703
Jay!

481
00:30:56,374 --> 00:30:57,958
Jasper!

482
00:30:57,958 --> 00:30:59,293
<i>Whatever!</i>

483
00:30:59,401 --> 00:31:00,652
Jean.

484
00:31:01,361 --> 00:31:02,488
<i>You jerk!</i>

485
00:31:03,190 --> 00:31:04,478
Mariano.

486
00:31:04,948 --> 00:31:06,073
<i>Whatever!</i>

487
00:31:07,618 --> 00:31:08,826
Watson.

488
00:31:11,205 --> 00:31:12,456
<i>That's you, not me.</i>

489
00:31:13,165 --> 00:31:15,793
Jasper Jean Mariano Watson.

490
00:31:15,793 --> 00:31:20,923
[Section E teasing]

491
00:31:20,923 --> 00:31:22,172
My wife.

492
00:31:25,052 --> 00:31:26,218
My life.

493
00:31:26,887 --> 00:31:28,680
All that sweetness is
rubbing on my cooking.

494
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:29,680
<i>Huh?</i>

495
00:31:31,615 --> 00:31:32,615
My everything.

496
00:31:33,101 --> 00:31:35,019
<i>What is he even talking about?</i>

497
00:31:38,063 --> 00:31:39,294
Pay attention, Jay.

498
00:31:39,310 --> 00:31:41,525
The food is salty but there
are ants everywhere.

499
00:31:42,355 --> 00:31:44,524
My food's starting to taste sweet!

500
00:31:44,702 --> 00:31:46,781
Whatever, assholes!

501
00:31:46,912 --> 00:31:48,497
Look at her, getting all giddy!

502
00:31:49,930 --> 00:31:52,558
Can you please add some more?

503
00:31:52,558 --> 00:31:53,930
Hey, hey!

504
00:32:04,069 --> 00:32:07,551
Hey, three dumbos!

505
00:32:09,422 --> 00:32:10,762
So you guys are here.

506
00:32:10,762 --> 00:32:12,097
No wonder you weren't downstairs.

507
00:32:12,097 --> 00:32:13,432
- The food is good.
- Jay.

508
00:32:14,100 --> 00:32:15,100
Why?

509
00:32:15,367 --> 00:32:16,659
Are you and Keifer together now?

510
00:32:19,804 --> 00:32:21,890
Seriously, are you two together?

511
00:32:23,436 --> 00:32:24,980
No.

512
00:32:26,695 --> 00:32:29,239
Ci-N just said earlier that there's
something between you two.

513
00:32:29,669 --> 00:32:31,087
Are you choosing Keifer?

514
00:32:31,815 --> 00:32:32,815
What about Yuri?

515
00:32:33,871 --> 00:32:35,289
You should've chosen him.

516
00:32:36,521 --> 00:32:38,400
I can't teach my heart
who to choose.

517
00:32:38,425 --> 00:32:39,426
Even so!

518
00:32:39,426 --> 00:32:41,052
You don't understand.

519
00:32:41,428 --> 00:32:42,846
What do you mean?

520
00:32:42,846 --> 00:32:44,505
Keifer will just hurt you.

521
00:32:45,432 --> 00:32:50,344
I just hope you won't regret
choosing him over Yuri.

522
00:32:53,857 --> 00:32:55,641
Section E is divided once again.

523
00:32:56,850 --> 00:32:59,394
I hope you don't get caught
in the middle of all this.

524
00:33:01,114 --> 00:33:02,114
Come on bro, let's go.

525
00:33:16,838 --> 00:33:20,624
<i>Will this be the same as the big
mess they had with Ella before?</i>

526
00:33:22,636 --> 00:33:23,887
<i>What have I done?</i>

527
00:33:24,888 --> 00:33:26,463
<i> Will it happen again?</i>

528
00:33:27,318 --> 00:33:29,800
<i>Will the home
we built fall apart?</i>

529
00:33:30,644 --> 00:33:31,831
